				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I personally dont like the idea myself. I dont believe any sort of balance can be made by centering around particular zones even if those zones are the best xp for us. The problems the pet faces follow us into Hard LDoNs and GoD too...
<br />

<br />
What you are asking for is situational pet upgrades that follow our class description. In essence you are asking for a mage-ified Dire Charm. We already voted no on that, iirc.
<br />

<br />
With that said, it also seems as though this system also forces us to either xp in a certain zone or use an undesirable pet ( like Earth pet in PoE when it would <span style="font-weight: bold">suck</span> to root a raid mob). Goes back about the balance issue of centering it on specific zones. Moreover the amount of procs and abilities you give the pet seems a bit overboard IMO. I would be happy with simply improved dmg/mitigation/resists. Especially some of the things you mentioned, like Whirl til You Hurl, Air Elemental Strike, Ice Storm, And Lava Splash would also be effects that could cause wipes on raids (Ooops my pet AEd those mezzed mobs, sorry for killing the encs~)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=746686" target="_blank" class="postlink">I am a gnome</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
