			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After reading the post by danille, I was thinking about how to make the epic pets, and other pets, "better".
<br />

<br />
1. Increase drop rates of epic pieces (OR reduce drop rates of other class epics ... hehe)
<br />

<br />
2. Reduce difficulty of some epic mobs (or should I say reduce difficulty in getting to or spawning epic mobs ... OR .... increase difficulty of other class epic mobs ... hehe). Examples of this is to not make the crown of air drop from the 7th isle, or to move ALL the epic drops for air to the 7th isle.
<br />

<br />
3. Alternative to 2 would be to make specific drops questable.
<br />

<br />
4. Upgrade the epic pet. For example a scaleable augment (much like the stone charm given by the old dwarf in POK) will enable you to summon a "better" epic pet (more hps, additional spells, faster attacks etc). The increases could depend on ... oh ... the numbers of quests that I have completed, zones I have visited, number of summoned bread I have eaten, etc. This augment could probably be used for all pet-class players.
<br />

<br />
5. Since some of the pet focus items are used in the epic quest .... the mage is left with the option of either going without the focus or gettig another focus (duh). Perhaps part of the "upgrading" could be that mages that have completed certain portions of their quest (eg after completing each section of the fire, earth, air and water ...) could be "flagged" to summon a better pet (after all, he has become a master of that element).
<br />

<br />
2 more coppers to the forum ... heh
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />

<br />
Deanorn on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
